{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769530926,"nonce":"iurQkBVZZDc8d7iEv6zA0dVvJPs=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mJ76f","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/65","origin":"github"},"title":"Protocol: Enforce 'File-First' for GitHub CLI Interactions","message":"Protocol: Enforce \"File-First\" for GitHub CLI Interactions\n\n## Problem\nRecent automated Issues and Pull Requests have suffered from markdown rendering errors. Specifically, newline characters (`\\n`) in multiline strings passed via CLI arguments are being escaped (e.g., becoming `\\\\n`), causing them to render as literal text instead of line breaks on GitHub.\n\n## Root Cause\nPassing complex, multiline strings directly to `gh` via the `--body` argument is fragile. Shells and the `run_command` tool execution layer can misinterpret or escape special characters.\n\n## Proposed Solution\nAgents MUST adopt a \"File-First\" approach for all complex GitHub interactions.\n\n1.  **Do not** pass content via `--body \"string\"`.\n2.  **Do** write content to a temporary file (e.g., `.agent/scratchpad/UNIQUE_ID.md`).\n3.  **Do** use the `--body-file` argument.\n\n## Action Items\n- [ ] Create a new rule file: `.agent/rules/common/github-cli-best-practices.md`.\n- [ ] Update `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` to reference this rule.\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Antigravity Agent`","files":null}]}